      "message": "Ideally darwinn would be it\u0027s own target that exports the right definition that lives in the darwinn directory.\n\nThat way we would just use android_target_link_libraries(android-emu linux-x86_64 PRIVATE darwinn). This will make it easier for us down the line to clean up android-emu (which is doing a bit much at the moment).\n\nit can be as simple as:\n\n\n\nset(darwinn_src android/darwinn/darwinn-service.cpp)\nandroid_add_library(darwinn)\ntarget_compile_options(darwinn PUBLIC \n                                   \"-DDARWINN_COMPILER_TEST_EXTERNAL\"\n                                   \"-DDARWINN_PORT_ANDROID_EMULATOR\u003d1\"\n                                   \"-DDARWINN_CHIP_TYPE\u003dUSB\"\n                                   \"-DDARWINN_CHIP_NAME\u003dbeagle\")\n\ntarget_link_libraries(darwinn PRIVATE darwinmoddelconfig)\ntarget_include_directories(darwinn PUBLIC include/dirs that propagate)\n\n\nand then have android_target_link_libraries(android-emu linux-x86_64 PRIVATE darwinn)\n\nSee also https://pabloariasal.github.io/2018/02/19/its-time-to-do-cmake-right/ for some background.",
